12:18.010 --> 12:20.180
- I don't know.

12:20.180 --> 12:22.000
It was the bottom left drawer?

12:22.000 --> 12:23.190
- Under some old files.

12:23.190 --> 12:25.160
Do you even remember the last
time you looked down there?

12:25.160 --> 12:28.020
- No!

12:28.020 --> 12:30.090
So somebody's framing me
or George.

12:30.090 --> 12:32.080
- Did George Vogelman
ever have access?

12:32.080 --> 12:34.070
Was he ever in the office alone?

12:34.070 --> 12:36.050
- It isn't him, Lindsay.

12:36.050 --> 12:37.160
- Can you really know that now?

12:37.160 --> 12:38.200
- Yes.

12:42.030 --> 12:45.160
- Okay.

12:45.160 --> 12:46.160
Arraignment's at 2:00.

12:46.160 --> 12:48.030
Division one.

12:48.030 --> 12:53.040
I can't imagine
they'll set bail, but--

12:53.040 --> 12:55.070
- I don't believe
this is really happening.

12:55.070 --> 12:57.200
A guy comes in,
he throws heroin at me,

12:57.200 --> 13:01.000
and I'm suddenly being held
for concealing a murder weapon?

13:01.000 --> 13:04.020
- It's gonna go away, Ellenor.

13:04.020 --> 13:05.210
Don't worry.

13:12.210 --> 13:14.060
- Can I help you?

13:14.060 --> 13:15.190
- I'm looking
for Dr. George Vogelman.

13:15.190 --> 13:18.120
Does he work here?
- He does, or did.

13:18.120 --> 13:20.080
You're about
ten minutes too late.

13:20.080 --> 13:22.180
- Sorry?
- The police just arrested him.

13:22.180 --> 13:25.160
Took him away.

13:25.160 --> 13:27.130
- The same charge: concealment.

13:27.130 --> 13:29.030
- And he's in custody?

13:29.030 --> 13:30.210
- Eugene's on his way
to see him in lockup.

13:30.210 --> 13:32.050
Lindsay talked to Helen.

13:32.050 --> 13:33.210
She thinks the police
are determined

13:33.210 --> 13:35.090
to get him all over again.

13:35.090 --> 13:37.070
Is concealment
a lesser included?

13:37.070 --> 13:38.070
- To murder?

13:38.070 --> 13:39.160
No way.
He's free game.

13:39.160 --> 13:40.170
- Bobby Donnell?

13:40.170 --> 13:42.000
- Yeah.

13:42.000 --> 13:44.090
- Milton Cables.
- Oh, hi.

13:44.090 --> 13:45.190
Thanks for agreeing to come.

13:45.190 --> 13:47.190
Uh, Jimmy Berluti.
- A pleasure.

13:47.190 --> 13:49.050
- As I said on the phone,
Judge Kittleson

13:49.050 --> 13:51.090
is very anxious
to dispose of this.

13:51.090 --> 13:53.010
- As is Mr. Michaels.

13:53.010 --> 13:55.000
He certainly doesn't want
to begin his law career

13:55.000 --> 13:57.090
as a plaintiff
in a sexual harassment case.

13:57.090 --> 13:58.230
That's why we filed under seal.

13:58.230 --> 14:00.130
- Which I appreciate.

14:00.130 --> 14:02.110
Listen, we've been hit
with a little emergency,

14:02.110 --> 14:03.230
and unfortunately,
I have to run out.

14:03.230 --> 14:06.170
If we could agree
to depose the two parties,

14:06.170 --> 14:08.070
also under seal,
do it right here,

14:08.070 --> 14:09.210
get some kind
of assessment on the case,

14:09.210 --> 14:12.190
we can pick a number
and be done.

14:12.190 --> 14:14.050
- Can she go first?

14:14.050 --> 14:17.000
- Sure, 6:00 tonight?
- Tonight?

14:17.000 --> 14:19.080
- You could always
depose her again if you want.

14:19.080 --> 14:21.170
My feeling is, if we could
flush out some facts quick,

14:21.170 --> 14:23.020
I think we could get rid of it.

14:23.020 --> 14:26.150
The faster the better
for both sides.

14:26.150 --> 14:28.130
- Okay, I'll see you
at 6:00 tonight.

14:28.130 --> 14:29.180
- Great.
Jimmy.

14:29.180 --> 14:32.020
Sorry to run out.

14:32.020 --> 14:33.180
- I'm so sorry.
- Leonard?

14:33.180 --> 14:35.040
- I never meant to hurt her.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.140
- Leonard,
you need to stop crying

14:36.140 --> 14:37.190
and listen to me.

14:37.190 --> 14:39.020
- I love Ellenor.

14:39.020 --> 14:40.140
- I know you do.

14:40.140 --> 14:42.190
And for you to help her,
you see,

14:42.190 --> 14:44.120
we may have to be
making statements

14:44.120 --> 14:47.000
that go against your interests,
which means you might need

14:47.000 --> 14:49.010
to get a new lawyer
for the time being.

14:49.010 --> 14:50.120
- I want Ellenor.

14:50.120 --> 14:52.000
- Well, Ellenor
isn't available right now.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.050
- I love Ellenor.
- She is in jail, Leonard.

14:54.050 --> 14:55.170
- She's always stuck by me.

14:55.170 --> 14:57.050
I can't--

14:57.050 --> 14:59.000
- Okay, well, what I am
trying to tell you is,

14:59.000 --> 15:02.050
we won't be sticking by you.

15:02.050 --> 15:04.110
- I love Ellenor.

15:04.110 --> 15:06.090
- Son of a bitch.

15:08.110 --> 15:10.150
- I have no idea.

15:10.150 --> 15:11.200
Want me to say it again?

15:11.200 --> 15:13.100
- Well, you better think,
George.

15:13.100 --> 15:14.230
Think who could have
stuck that knife in that drawer.

15:14.230 --> 15:16.110
Otherwise--
- I've heard that speech.

15:16.110 --> 15:17.230
"You better think, George!

15:17.230 --> 15:19.050
"Better think who could have
put that head

15:19.050 --> 15:22.080
in your medical bag,
otherwise--"

15:22.080 --> 15:25.130
- Now is not the time
to get snide.

15:25.130 --> 15:28.130
This is Ellenor on the line now,
not just you.

15:28.130 --> 15:30.220
- I know that.

15:30.220 --> 15:33.160
Why would I ever
put a knife in her drawer?

15:33.160 --> 15:37.010
Or if I did give it to her,
why would she even take it?

15:37.010 --> 15:38.170
Somebody's doing something here.

15:38.170 --> 15:40.190
- And you can't think of
who it could possibly be?

15:40.190 --> 15:44.060
- No.

15:44.060 --> 15:45.150
- George, I'll tell you this.

15:45.150 --> 15:47.220
If I ever get wind--
- You'll what?

15:47.220 --> 15:49.050
Beat me up?

15:49.050 --> 15:50.140
Do it.

15:50.140 --> 15:52.060
I've been out of work
for six months.

15:52.060 --> 15:53.200
I finally got hired
two days ago.

15:53.200 --> 15:56.060
Two days ago,
and what happens?

15:56.060 --> 15:59.050
In come the police
to take me away again.

15:59.050 --> 16:01.020
Go ahead, Eugene,
beat the hell out of me.

16:01.020 --> 16:02.190
I need the money.

16:06.060 --> 16:08.170
WOMAN: Case number 32632.

16:08.170 --> 16:10.080
Commonwealth versus
Ellenor Frutt.

16:10.080 --> 16:11.170
- Bobby Donnell
for the defense, Your Honor.

16:11.170 --> 16:13.040
Waive reading.

16:13.040 --> 16:14.080
I ask that this court
dismiss all charges

16:14.080 --> 16:15.080
on the grounds--

16:15.080 --> 16:16.180
- Dismiss, dismiss.

16:16.180 --> 16:18.100
Everybody's getting up
and asking me

16:18.100 --> 16:19.180
to dismiss charges.

16:19.180 --> 16:21.030
What do I look like, hmm?

16:21.030 --> 16:22.210
- Well, under
the circumstances, I--

16:22.210 --> 16:24.040
- I've already dismissed charges

16:24.040 --> 16:25.100
against this woman once today.

16:25.100 --> 16:27.050
That's all she gets.

16:27.050 --> 16:28.200
I don't just kick things here,

16:28.200 --> 16:30.090
especially in murder cases.

16:30.090 --> 16:31.140
Not dismissed.

16:31.140 --> 16:34.000
No, no, no!

16:34.000 --> 16:37.170
- What do you mean,
"murder case"?

16:37.170 --> 16:40.070
- Yes, it's murder
your client is charged with,

16:40.070 --> 16:41.070
first-degree murder.

16:41.070 --> 16:42.140
If you didn't know that,

16:42.140 --> 16:44.070
why the hell
did you waive reading?

16:44.070 --> 16:48.030
- What's going on here?

16:48.030 --> 16:49.150
What is going on?

16:49.150 --> 16:52.000
MAN: Talk to me, Counselor.

16:52.000 --> 16:53.190
Never mind, don't.

16:53.190 --> 16:56.060
Now I'm mad, all right?

16:56.060 --> 16:58.030
Next case.
Give me something good.

16:58.030 --> 16:59.190
- What the hell is this?

16:59.190 --> 17:03.060
- Why don't we
find a room to talk?

17:08.210 --> 17:10.010
- There's enough there.

17:10.010 --> 17:11.150
- For a murder charge?

17:11.150 --> 17:12.230
- Well, I'm not saying
we're gonna make,

17:12.230 --> 17:14.130
but we got to face
a few facts here.

17:14.130 --> 17:16.170
She had a romantic relationship
with this Vogelman.

17:16.170 --> 17:18.040
- That was two years ago.

17:18.040 --> 17:19.220
- Well, love's been
known to smolder.

17:19.220 --> 17:21.069
- Is this a joke?

17:21.069 --> 17:23.010
- She's found
with the murder weapon,

17:23.010 --> 17:26.180
and we all know
Ellenor has a temper.

17:26.180 --> 17:29.210
- What do you want, Richard?

17:29.210 --> 17:31.090
- Vogelman.

17:31.090 --> 17:33.100
She testifies that
he gave her the knife,

17:33.100 --> 17:35.120
well, maybe we can
make things go easy on her.

17:35.120 --> 17:36.200
- First of all,
I have no knowledge

17:36.200 --> 17:37.220
that he gave her the knife.

17:37.220 --> 17:39.100
Second, you can't get Vogelman.

17:39.100 --> 17:40.200
Double jeopardy.

17:40.200 --> 17:42.050
- Oh, we can't
get him on murder,

17:42.050 --> 17:43.160
but we can on concealment
and perjury.

17:43.160 --> 17:46.000
- Third, this is
blatant blackmail.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.140
- This is a settlement
negotiation.

17:48.140 --> 17:52.200
- You're charging a lawyer
with murder to get her client?

17:52.200 --> 17:54.160
This is way over the line.

17:54.160 --> 17:56.150
- Bobby, you guys accused
a victim's brother of murder

17:56.150 --> 17:58.010
just to get your client off,

17:58.010 --> 17:59.160
and you want to debate
where the line is?

17:59.160 --> 18:00.170
- We're defense attorneys.

18:00.170 --> 18:02.030
It's different.

18:02.030 --> 18:05.000
- Discuss the offer
with Ellenor

18:05.000 --> 18:06.140
and then get back to me.

18:12.170 --> 18:14.010
- I don't believe it.

18:14.010 --> 18:15.040
- I've got
the motion to suppress

18:15.040 --> 18:16.090
marked up for tomorrow.

18:16.090 --> 18:17.200
- With that judge?
- No, thank God.

18:17.200 --> 18:19.060
Judge West.

18:19.060 --> 18:20.140
- How is George?
- Not good.

18:20.140 --> 18:21.140
They denied bail.

18:21.140 --> 18:23.020
- For concealing evidence?

18:23.020 --> 18:24.140
- And perjury,
obstruction of justice.

18:24.140 --> 18:25.170
They're on a mission, Bobby.

18:25.170 --> 18:27.050
They're out for him,

18:27.050 --> 18:29.090
and now they have
the perfect chance.

18:34.220 --> 18:36.190
- So you don't deny the affair?

18:36.190 --> 18:38.150
- No, I don't.

18:38.150 --> 18:40.220
Nor did I regret it
until yesterday.

18:40.220 --> 18:42.150
- Can you tell us
how your relationship

18:42.150 --> 18:44.030
with Kevin Michaels began?

18:44.030 --> 18:45.170
- Our professional
relationship began

18:45.170 --> 18:47.000
when I hired him
out of law school

18:47.000 --> 18:48.180
to clerk for me.

18:48.180 --> 18:52.100
Our physical relationship
began about four months later.

18:52.100 --> 18:54.050
It was a Friday night.

18:54.050 --> 18:55.220
We were going over a draft

18:55.220 --> 18:59.010
of a rather convoluted opinion
regarding stock fraud,

18:59.010 --> 19:03.180
and uh, well,

19:03.180 --> 19:07.140
I suppose one might say
I seduced him.

19:07.140 --> 19:09.200
- Why might one say that?

19:09.200 --> 19:11.160
- Because I did.

19:15.130 --> 19:17.180
- Can you be more specific?

19:17.180 --> 19:19.040
- Do I need to be?

19:19.040 --> 19:20.150
The basis of this lawsuit

19:20.150 --> 19:23.110
concerns what happened
after he left my employ.

19:23.110 --> 19:25.150
We can all stipulate
to the sexual affair.

19:25.150 --> 19:28.030
- We're on a fast course
to settle this.

19:28.030 --> 19:30.020
I need to flesh out
some of the background

19:30.020 --> 19:31.200
before advising my client.

19:38.150 --> 19:40.120
- All right.

19:40.120 --> 19:44.190
We were working side by side
going over this draft.

19:44.190 --> 19:46.160
He reached across
for something--

19:46.160 --> 19:49.180
I don't remember what--

19:49.180 --> 19:52.170
and he inadvertently
brushed my breast.

19:52.170 --> 19:54.180
He began to apologize profusely,

19:54.180 --> 19:58.120
and perhaps to dissipate
his embarrassment,

19:58.120 --> 20:01.080
I said,
"Don't be sorry.

20:01.080 --> 20:02.210
I rather enjoyed it."

20:06.120 --> 20:09.030
- What--what happened next?

20:09.030 --> 20:10.230
- Well, he just
stared back at me.

20:10.230 --> 20:14.130
I had obviously shocked him.

20:14.130 --> 20:17.100
But he had an expression,

20:17.100 --> 20:21.230
almost as if he were
titillated a little as well.

20:23.100 --> 20:26.190
And, oh,
I don't know.

20:26.190 --> 20:28.130
Maybe because the hour was late

20:28.130 --> 20:31.030
and my senses were fried,

20:31.030 --> 20:34.150
or--or it was
just the dare in me.

20:34.150 --> 20:38.150
I said, "It's not
the worst thing in life

20:38.150 --> 20:41.130
to be touched, you know?"

20:44.140 --> 20:49.030
And I reached out my hand.

20:49.030 --> 20:52.000
I touched him

20:52.000 --> 20:57.070
and said,
"Not so bad, is it?"

21:00.110 --> 21:01.110
- And then?

21:01.110 --> 21:05.070
- And then, uh,

21:05.070 --> 21:08.090
at the risk
of sounding immodest,

21:08.090 --> 21:13.160
I gave him the best fellatio
known to mankind.

21:24.220 --> 21:26.140
I am sorry to be so blunt,

21:26.140 --> 21:29.160
but I think we all know
what can happen

21:29.160 --> 21:32.180
if you don't come clean
at a deposition.

21:44.020 --> 21:45.060
- No prints on the knife.

21:45.060 --> 21:46.120
DNA was positive.

21:46.120 --> 21:47.220
It's Susan Robin's blood.

21:47.220 --> 21:49.110
- Great.

21:49.110 --> 21:51.070
- I think Vogelman
needs independent counsel.

21:51.070 --> 21:52.070
- For now--

21:52.070 --> 21:53.070
- What if we need to argue

21:53.070 --> 21:54.080
he put the knife in here?

21:54.080 --> 21:55.090
My money says we will.

21:55.090 --> 21:56.150
- Let's just see how

21:56.150 --> 21:58.030
the suppression hearing
goes on Ellenor.

21:58.030 --> 22:00.090
If we win there,
there won't be any conflict.

22:03.140 --> 22:05.220
You all set?
- Yep.

22:05.220 --> 22:08.110
- Do you need any help
on any research or--

22:08.110 --> 22:10.200
- I'm fine.

22:10.200 --> 22:12.130
- Lindsay,
it's a good case to take.

22:12.130 --> 22:14.220
If a judge hires you,
that's a nice feather.

22:14.220 --> 22:16.070
- It's under seal, Bobby.

22:16.070 --> 22:18.050
There's no marquee value
in this case.

22:18.050 --> 22:20.220
There was no reason to take it.

22:20.220 --> 22:22.080
Or was there?

22:22.080 --> 22:24.090
- Oh, please,
you can't be jealous.

22:24.090 --> 22:25.160
- Bobby,
let me just concentrate

22:25.160 --> 22:27.170
on Ellenor's case
right now, okay?

22:30.020 --> 22:31.220
- Your Honor.
- Am I early?

22:31.220 --> 22:34.180
- No, uh--no, we're set to go
in about 20 minutes,

22:34.180 --> 22:36.140
and Bobby wanted
to go over some stuff.

22:36.140 --> 22:38.150
- Do you perhaps have something
I could just nibble?

22:38.150 --> 22:40.210
Oh, hello.

22:40.210 --> 22:41.230
- Hello.

22:41.230 --> 22:42.230
Could I get by?

22:42.230 --> 22:45.130
- Oh, terribly sorry.

22:45.130 --> 22:47.120
- I'll be down as soon as I can.

22:58.030 --> 22:59.210
- I don't mean to add pressure,

22:59.210 --> 23:02.090
but if we don't win this,
Ellenor faces a long haul.

23:02.090 --> 23:03.220
- I know.

23:03.220 --> 23:06.110
Do you have any idea
how that knife got there?

23:06.110 --> 23:08.190
- It had to be George.

23:12.010 --> 23:13.190
BOBBY: You never
showed him the letter?

23:13.190 --> 23:16.230
- Not before I sent it out.

23:16.230 --> 23:18.190
I suppose I should have.

23:18.190 --> 23:21.220
This isn't about
that letter, Bobby.

23:21.220 --> 23:23.080
You read it.

23:23.080 --> 23:25.030
It may not have been
laced with superlatives,

23:25.030 --> 23:26.170
but it certainly
wasn't critical.

23:26.170 --> 23:30.190
- Well, he's suing you
for it, so--

23:30.190 --> 23:33.220
- My bet is, he's suing
just for the privilege

23:33.220 --> 23:35.230
of these depositions.

23:35.230 --> 23:39.120
He gets to be in the same room
with me again.

23:39.120 --> 23:41.220
I don't think he's over me,
to tell you the truth.

23:47.100 --> 23:49.170
Is everything okay?

23:49.170 --> 23:50.150
- Fine.

23:56.040 --> 23:57.220
- They had no warrant
to search that desk.

23:57.220 --> 23:59.060
- And nor is one required.

23:59.060 --> 24:00.170
It was a search
incident to an arrest.

24:00.170 --> 24:03.090
Warrantless searches--
- Hold on a second.

24:03.090 --> 24:06.220
Are you saying the arrest
of Ms. Frutt was invalid?

24:06.220 --> 24:08.060
- On the knife,
absolutely.

24:08.060 --> 24:10.020
- Not on the knife.
On the drugs.

24:10.020 --> 24:11.130
- That case was dismissed.

24:11.130 --> 24:13.040
- I understand,
but are you saying

24:13.040 --> 24:15.210
at the time the arrest was made,
it was legally invalid?

24:15.210 --> 24:17.230
- Yes, they knew
those drugs weren't hers.

24:17.230 --> 24:20.150
- The heroin
was on her desk, Counsel.

24:20.150 --> 24:22.180
There was no probable cause
for an arrest?

24:22.180 --> 24:24.110
- They came in chasing
somebody else for those drugs.

24:24.110 --> 24:25.220
He ran right to this desk.

24:25.220 --> 24:27.080
They see the drugs
on top of the desk.

24:27.080 --> 24:28.230
They suddenly think
they belong to her.

24:28.230 --> 24:31.010
Please, that insults
everybody's intelligence.

24:31.010 --> 24:32.230
- Which is why the case
on the drugs

24:32.230 --> 24:34.230
was ultimately dismissed.

24:34.230 --> 24:37.210
But if the arrest was
technically valid at the time,

24:37.210 --> 24:40.030
then so was the search
that turned up the knife.

24:40.030 --> 24:41.190
- Even if you were
to uphold the search

24:41.190 --> 24:44.180
as incident to a valid arrest,
the area to be searched

24:44.180 --> 24:47.000
has to be within the control
of the suspect.

24:47.000 --> 24:49.020
- Which this was.
It was her desk.

24:49.020 --> 24:50.050
- She wasn't
even in the building

24:50.050 --> 24:51.170
by the time you found the knife,

24:51.170 --> 24:53.100
so the desk couldn't be
within her control.

24:53.100 --> 24:55.030
- The search
began contemporaneously

24:55.030 --> 24:56.030
with the arrest.

24:56.030 --> 24:57.120
It continued after she left.

24:57.120 --> 24:59.060
It did not begin after she left.

24:59.060 --> 25:00.150
There's a difference,
Your Honor.

25:00.150 --> 25:01.130
I can cite the cases.

25:01.130 --> 25:03.000
- None of those cases

25:03.000 --> 25:05.070
involved a pretext arrest,
which this was.

25:05.070 --> 25:06.150
They knew the drugs
weren't hers.

25:06.150 --> 25:07.160
They didn't have
a good-faith basis

25:07.160 --> 25:08.230
to make that arrest.

25:08.230 --> 25:10.050
Any search
incident to that arrest

25:10.050 --> 25:12.100
is also lacking in good faith.

25:12.100 --> 25:15.090
This is part of a master plan
to get George Vogelman,

25:15.090 --> 25:17.020
and everybody
in this room knows it.

25:17.020 --> 25:18.100
- Objection!
- Make your objection,

25:18.100 --> 25:19.200
but I am putting this
on the record.

25:19.200 --> 25:21.020
They charge her with murder,

25:21.020 --> 25:22.170
and they offer
to drop everything

25:22.170 --> 25:24.170
if she would flip
George Vogelman on concealment.

25:24.170 --> 25:26.080
